        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#maffre2007"/>, p. 178, n. <citedRange>45</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>57.2002, 10</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015a"/>, p. <citedRange>74</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>006000</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo_Myrtoios"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλλω</supplied><unclear>ν</unclear>ι</name> 
                        <rs type="epithet" key="Myrtoios"><name nymRef="#Μυρτῶιος">Μυρτ<unclear>ώ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ιωι</supplied></name></rs></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem resp="#cdl2015a"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλλω</supplied><unclear>ν</unclear>ι Μυρτ<unclear>ώ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ιωι</supplied></lem>
                    <rdg resp="#maffre2007"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ν Μυρτό<supplied reason="lost">ο</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg></app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>À Apollon Myrtoos <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>To Apollo Myrtoos <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Per Apollo Myrtoos <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>From the photograph one can clearly see at left end a small part of nu, followed by iota, whereas the last letter at right end should be 
                 a round letter with a crooked summit, for which omega would be a good candidate, in agreement with the date of the ceramics.</p>
             <p>Apollo Myrtoos also appears much later, in a dedication to the emperor Nero, cf. <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.288.html">IRCyr2020 C.288</ref>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
